\section{Conclusion}
In this paper we have proposed an optimal strategy for finding an orthonormal basis for the Graph Fourier Transform based on the minimization of the graph cut set size as a way to emphasize clustering properties of graph signals.
We have shown that the optimal solution can be found  by solving a
sequence of  exact convex problems without any loss of optimality.
Numerical results prove that the resulting Fourier basis is able to grasp the sharp variations of
graph signal across clusters as well as their smoothness within each cluster.

